05830nam a22009015i 9783035619447DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20202020sz     fo  d z      eng d  a97830356194477 a10.1515/97830356194472doi  a(DE-B1597)517863  a(OCoLC)1197980501  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 4aNA8240b.Z84 202004a725/.372231 aZwerger, Klaus, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aCereal Drying Racks :bCulture and Typology of Wood Buildings in Europe and East Asia /cKlaus Zwerger. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (360 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tForeword -- tIntroduction -- t1 The Cereal Drying Rack – Terminology and Typology -- t2 Functions of the Cereal Drying Rack -- t3 Cultural Context -- t4 Occurrence and Distribution -- t5 Structure and Construction -- t6 Drying Rack Typologies in Europe -- t7 Drying Rack Typologies in Asia -- t8 Roofing -- t9 Characteristic Differences between Cereal Drying Racks in the West and East -- t10 Closing remarks -- tAPPENDIX0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAnschließend an sein Buch Das Holz und seine Verbindungen, das seit mehr als 20 Jahren ein Grundlagenwerk für den reinen Holzbau darstellt und in der 3. Auflage vorliegt, widmet sich Klaus Zwerger hier der Geschichte, Konstruktion und Typologie eines besonderen Bautyps: Die Getreideharfen dienten in den agrarischen Kulturen vieler Länder und Kontinente zum Trocknen des geschnittenen Getreides. Über Jahrhunderte bildeten sich ebenso ausgereifte wie individuelle Bauten von großer Schönheit in ihrer funktionalen Effizienz heraus. Auf zahllosen Reisen hat der Autor die heute noch erhaltenen Bauten aufgespürt. In detaillierten Beschreibungen, eingebettet in bau- und kulturgeschichtliche Zusammenhänge, kommen sie ebenso zur Geltung wie in den in Duoton wiedergegebenen Schwarzweißfotografien und Strichzeichnungen.  aFollowing his seminal book Wood and Wood Joints, an essential reference on solid timber constructions for more than two decades, now in its third edition, Klaus Zwerger presents a study of the cultural history, construction and typology of a special building type: cereal drying racks. These structures were used to dry harvested crops in agrarian cultures all over the world and evolved over the centuries into buildings of great beauty that are as sophisticated and individual as they are functionally efficient. On countless expeditions, the author tracked down the remaining buildings, documenting and analyzing them in the context of their cultural and building history through detailed descriptions, line drawings and photographs, rendered in duotone, by the author.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aGrainxDryingzEast Asia. 0aGrainxDryingzEurope. 0aGranarieszEast Asia. 0aGranarieszEurope. 0aWooden-frame buildingszEast Asia. 0aWooden-frame buildingszEurope.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertArt and Architecture eBook-Package 2020z978311073823008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2020z9783110704679oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2020 Englishz978311070478508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gru